Third-party components
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project orchestrates and builds on the following open-source projects. It
does not redistribute their source, but its trainer/inference container images
install them at build time. Each retains its own license:

  * nnU-Net v2 (nnunetv2)            — Apache-2.0
  * TotalSegmentator (code)          — Apache-2.0
  * batchgenerators / batchgeneratorsv2 — Apache-2.0
  * MLflow                           — Apache-2.0
  * Kueue                            — Apache-2.0
  * KubeRay / Ray                    — Apache-2.0
  * SimpleITK                        — Apache-2.0
  * nibabel                          — MIT
  * pydantic, click, jinja2, pyyaml, rich — MIT / BSD-style

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT — model weight licensing (read before shipping trained models)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TotalSegmentator distributes pretrained weights under MIXED licenses:

  * CT weights : CC-BY-4.0          — commercial use OK, attribution required
  * MR weights : CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0    — NON-COMMERCIAL ONLY

Any model fine-tuned from TotalSegmentator MR weights inherits the
CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 non-commercial restriction. If you intend to use models
commercially, do not derive them from upstream MR weights. Tag every
registered model with its `base_model` and `dataset_license` so lineage stays
auditable. See docs/licensing.md.

Public datasets used in the examples (MSD, PDDCA, LUNA16, BTCV, TotalSegmentator,
SegRap, etc.) each carry their own terms — consult the dataset provider before
redistribution or commercial use.
